 within the larger currents of liberal theory and integrates them into a general stance toward freedom, gender equality, and religious pluralism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674036581?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674036581423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674036581/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK